title: TypeError when using Refine Outliers
body:
### Is there an existing issue for this?

- [X] I have searched the existing issues

### Bug description

I exctracted ~50 frames manually using the Extract Outliers GUI. When I clicked Launch GUI and attempted to load the machinelabels h5 file I get the traceback shown below. I completed a clean install of both the code, and the environment neither of which rectified the issue. I also double checked that the config file pointed to the correct video and the labels are also in the correct place. I saw this error on other time on our GPU compute cluster but a fresh install fixed it there. The same DLC installation was used to extract the labels as we tried to use to refine them. 

### Operating System

Windows 10

### DeepLabCut version

dlc version: 2.2.0.6

### DeepLabCut mode

single animal

### Device type

CPU

### Steps To Reproduce

1. Successfully Extract Outlier Frames
2. Launch the Outlier Labeling GUI using LAUNCH GUI
3. Select the machinelabels-iter0.h5 file in the appropriate labeled-data folder for our video
4. Get the stack trace below and the program locks up

### Relevant log output

```shell
`Traceback (most recent call last):
  File "C:\Users\dewanlab.PSY-PDB-C474-B\anaconda3\envs\DEEPLABCUT\lib\site-packages\deeplabcut\gui\refinement.py", line 395, in browseDir
    self.Dataframe.sort_index(inplace=True)
  File "C:\Users\dewanlab.PSY-PDB-C474-B\anaconda3\envs\DEEPLABCUT\lib\site-packages\pandas\util\_decorators.py", line 311, in wrapper
    return func(*args, **kwargs)
  File "C:\Users\dewanlab.PSY-PDB-C474-B\anaconda3\envs\DEEPLABCUT\lib\site-packages\pandas\core\frame.py", line 6449, in sort_index
    return super().sort_index(
  File "C:\Users\dewanlab.PSY-PDB-C474-B\anaconda3\envs\DEEPLABCUT\lib\site-packages\pandas\core\generic.py", line 4693, in sort_index
    indexer = get_indexer_indexer(
  File "C:\Users\dewanlab.PSY-PDB-C474-B\anaconda3\envs\DEEPLABCUT\lib\site-packages\pandas\core\sorting.py", line 93, in get_indexer_indexer
    indexer = nargsort(
  File "C:\Users\dewanlab.PSY-PDB-C474-B\anaconda3\envs\DEEPLABCUT\lib\site-packages\pandas\core\sorting.py", line 411, in nargsort
    indexer = non_nan_idx[non_nans.argsort(kind=kind)]
TypeError: '<' not supported between instances of 'str' and 'tuple'`
```

_No response_
